            <title>[CASSANDRA-19439] Non-serial reads need to handle racing with Accord topology changes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19439</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A key or range read could end up being sent to Accord when it&apos;s not managed by Accord and we might not find out until the execution epoch is known. In reality I think this already throws an exception in Accord for a key we just need to propagate and handle the exception and retry with the new topology until we can complete the read.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
